{"key":"post-19495763","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>19495763</id>\n<content>Experience from myself and other growers have shown the point of diminishing returns with &lt;i&gt;P cubensis&lt;/i&gt; starts at a substrate depth of around 3 to 4 inches if using coir, compost, manure, etc.&amp;nbsp; With straw, you can use a much deeper substrate, but anything over 12&quot; or so runs the risk of the core becoming anaerobic and starting to rot.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The age-old argument over whether two 4&quot; deep substrates will outperform one 8&quot; deep substrate will be hashed and re-hashed forever, but my money is on the two shallower ones.&amp;nbsp; Experiment away.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>19495777</next>\n<prev>19495707</prev>\n<first>19495424</first>\n<last>19515770</last>\n<when>1391102539</when>\n<utime>01/30/14 07:22 PM</utime>\n</post>"}